snippet: Security fears had kept the agents from traveling from the American Embassy in Tripoli, the Libyan capital, to collect evidence in Benghazi.
abstract: Federal Bureau of Investigation agents enter ruins of American diplomatic compound in Benghazi, Libya, as they investigate the killings of Ambassador J Christopher Stevens and three other Americans; security fears had kept the agents from traveling to crime scene; delay was also partly caused by slow approval process of the Libyan government.

byline.original: By ELISABETH BUMILLER and MICHAEL S. SCHMIDT
